  "original_title": "\u2019\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Sri Lanka's situation is a lesson for all'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Prime Minister of Malaysia Mahathir Mohamad has said that Sri Lanka's current debt crisis is a warning to the governments of other Asian countries and that everyone should follow a responsible fiscal policy, otherwise they will end up in the hands of the International Monetary Fund.",
        "The South Asian nation (Sri Lanka) has run out of foreign exchange reserves to pay for imports, which has led to political instability and food and fuel shortages in the country. He also said that the country has stopped paying its foreign debt and has started negotiations for an IMF loan.",
        "Sri Lanka's main problem is that Sri Lanka has very little currency reserves to pay its creditors, which is entirely the result of poor currency management and poor investment policy, he said. So all are threatened by the possibility of going down Sri Lanka's path. He also said that this is a lesson for everyone."
      ],
